<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's the glamorous AFL WAG who enjoys the finer things in life. </p>

<p>And it seems Rebecca Judd, 37, has already passed her expensive taste onto her three-year-old son Tom. </p>

<p>On Monday's 3pm Pick Up, the mother-of-four left her co-host Katie 'Monty' Dimond in hysterics after revealing Tom's very snobby response to hearing Drake's new song Popstar.  </p>

<p>Expensive taste! Footy WAG Rebecca Judd, 37, (right) has revealed her three-year-old son Tom's (left) VERY snobby response to hearing the word 'lobster' in Drake's new rap song Popstar </p>

<p>'I played it to my twins Tom and Darcy this morning and this was their reaction,' Rebecca said, playing a segment of Drake's song where he raps the phrase: 'Busy at the crib, cookin' salmon with the lobster.' </p>

<p>'Lobster! I like eating lobster,' Tom can be heard exclaiming in the background of the recording.  </p>

<p>'A three-year-old but I like eating lobster! Of course that is a Judd kid saying that. Out of everything, that's what he notices!' chuckled Monty. </p>

<p>'Of course that is a Judd kid saying that': On Monday's 3pm Pick Up, Rebecca co-host Katie 'Monty' Dimond in hysterics after sharing a recording of Tom exclaiming: 'Lobster! I like eating lobster!' </p>

<p>Setting the record straight! Rebecca (pictured at a Japanese restaurant with twin sons Tom and Darcy) interjected: 'For the record, he has never tried lobster in his life' </p>

<p>Rebecca, who lives in a $7.3million mansion in Melbourne's affluent suburb of Brighton, interjected: 'For the record, he has never tried lobster in his life.' </p>

<p>'Sure!' Monty quipped.</p>

<p>Rebecca continued, insisting that somehow Tom just 'gravitated towards' the phrase about lobsters.  </p>

<p>At home restaurant! In April, Rebecca revealed on Instagram that she's been feeding her family with restaurant-quality food from Melbourne Crown's Atlantic Group during COVID-19 lockdown</p>

<p>While Tom may not have eaten the expensive crustacean before, he is no stranger to high-class dining. </p>

<p>In April, Rebecca revealed on Instagram that she's been feeding her family with restaurant-quality food from Melbourne Crown's Atlantic Group during COVID-19 lockdown.   </p>

<p>Proving that tins of spaghetti were the last thing served at her Melbourne mansion, as she showcased the expensive, home-delivered meals on Instagram.</p>

<p>Fancy feast: In July, Rebecca also treated her family to a decadent home-delivered high tea, making sure to show off the lavish spread on Instagram</p>

<p>In July, Rebecca also treated her family to a decadent home-delivered high tea, making sure to show off the lavish spread on Instagram. </p>

<p>Rebecca and her AFL star husband Chris Judd share their four children, son Oscar, eight, daughter Billie, five, and twin sons Tom and Darcy, three. </p>

<p>The 3pm Pick-Up airs on the KIIS Network from 3pm to 4pm weekdays. </p>

